  "texts": [
    "KiDZ VISTA observing programmeIn order to produce NIR observations in the KiDZ fields that are consistent with those existing in the KiDS fields, we undertook a A170, page 16 of 54 campaign to obtain VIKING-like data over the KiDZ fields from 5 December 2016 to 2 October 2018 (see Table 7), with the same observing constraints and settings as the VIKING survey itself (i.e.",
    "Figure 6 shows the distribution of these dedicated VISTA observations in each of the KiDZ fields, as green boxes.The areas of the KiDZ fields that are not covered by these dedicated observations, but which nonetheless contain both optical and NIR data (shown by the dark grey), consist of VIKINGlike data that was reconstructed from pre-existing deep VISTA observations in these fields (Sect. 4.1.3).",
    "KiDS-VIKING pipeline reductionThe NIR data in KiDS+KiDZ were reduced with the same reduction pipeline used in previous KiDS data releases: KVPIPE (Wright et al. 2018), based on the processing pipeline developed in Driver et al.",
    "(2016) for GAMA.",
    "We opted to start from the reduced CASU paw-prints, because of the complex observing strategy and dither pattern of VISTA observations: within one tile there is a wide range of total exposure times (between 1× and 6× the individual exposure times, t exp) and observational properties (up to 96 different PSFs)."
